Upwards of 40% of jobs could be displaced by technology. We need a plan so our workforce can maintain their edge in a global economy. The #FutureOfWork starts now. pic.twitter.com/tMybldwsCY
Yesterday, we launched the  #FOWCaucus to give workers the skills they need to stay ahead as artificial intelligence begins to impact jobs from manufacturing to financial services.

Every child deserves a safe place to call home, and I’m grateful to have partners at the local, state and federal level fighting to #EndHomelessness. Today @HUDgov announced $107 million in grants to #Ohio to support places like @Huck_House in #OH15. More:  https://bit.ly/2tXBIQ0  pic.twitter.com/EUIzdPi1va

The deadline for submissions is March 3. See if your school or entity qualifies for funding here:  http://bit.ly/2FNpT1g 

If you have questions about the submission process, call my Hilliard office at (614) 771-4968.

The FY20 spending bill secured $125M for the STOP School Violence Act, a bill I was proud to cosponsor, to create safer environments for students through prevention & mental health efforts. This funding will get critical resources to schools, law enforcement, & health providers.

2019 was memorable, some highlights include:

✅More jobs
✅Passed USMCA
✅Introduced legislation to pair veterans with service dogs
